      "author": "vincentlaucsb",
      "description": "### Added\r\n\r\n- Added protection for unsaved CSV edits in the embedded Obsidian viewer.\r\n- The plugin now listens for dirty-state messages from the local `csvzall` viewer.\r\n- When a CSV has unsaved changes, navigating away, opening another file in the pane, or closing the view now asks for confirmation before discarding edits.\r\n\r\n### Changed\r\n\r\n- Updated README feature descriptions for chart generation, chart regeneration, and SQLite querying.\r\n- Added README limitations for large CSV editing and multi-value chart configuration.\r\n- Switched the README logo to the theme-safe csvzall logo.\r\n- Updated release metadata for version `0.1.2`.\r\n\r\n### Compatibility\r\n\r\n- Minimum Obsidian version remains `1.5.0`.",
